       "img-caption"> Greatest Boxer of All Time </p>
    
    <p> Muhammad Ali Born on January 17, 1942 Louisville, Kentucky, Died June 3, 2016. Muhammad was professional boxer Nicknamed "The Greatest".

Muhammad was know the best heavyweight boxer of the 20th century , he also won a gold medal in the light heavyweight divison at the 1960 Olympics.

He converted to Islam and became a Muslim after 1961, and changed his name from Cassius Marellus Clay Jr. to Muhammad Ali. <br> <br>

He won the world heavyweight Championship from Sonny Liston in at the age of 22 in 1964.

The only Boxer to get Ring magazine Fighter of the Year six times is Ali, He has been ranked the greatest heavyweight boxer of all time,
and as the greatest athlete of the 20th century by Sports Illustrated, 
the Sports Personality of the Century by the BBC, and the third greatest athlete of the 20th century by ESPN SportsCentury. </p>
    
